headline: Stanley Fischer, who spread the macroeconomic gospel, dies at 81
summary: (Bloomberg) -- Stanley Fischer, a professor and practitioner of macroeconomics who helped guide central banks in two countries, Israel and the US, and mentored a younger generation of economic decision-makers, has died.
